Former Likoni Member of Parliament Salim Khalif Mwavumo has died. Mwavumo passed on at his home in Kizingo, Mombasa County, on Monday morning. The deceased served as Likoni MP between 1992-1997 after winning the seat on a Ford Kenya party ticket. Mombasa businessman Suleiman Shahbal mourned the deceased terming him the leader of Likoni Elders and saying he was like a father to him. “He served with my uncle as a councilor in the defunct Municipal Council of Mombasa in the early 1960s. I valued his wise counsel,” said Shahbal. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis